---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { LINKS } from '../config/links';

const title = "The Money Story Method — 12-Week Behavioural Coaching Programme | Way of Wealth";
const description = "A 1:1 coaching programme for men who've tried budgets, apps, and spreadsheets — and still feel stuck. MSc Behavioral Economics | Qualified Financial Planner.";

// Founding cohort counters — Joel updates these manually and pushes when a spot fills.
const FOUNDING_SPOTS_REMAINING = 5;
const FOUNDING_APPLICANTS = 0;
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={`${LINKS.siteUrl}/coaching`}>

<!-- HERO (credential strip merged in) -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-credential">MSc Behavioral Economics &nbsp;|&nbsp; Qualified Financial Planner (UK)</div>
  <p class="hero-tag">The Money Story Method</p>
  <h1>A 12-week programme for people who've <em>tried everything else.</em></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">1:1 behavioural coaching that goes deeper than budgets. For anyone who knows what they <em>should</em> be doing with money — and keeps hitting the same wall before they can.</p>
  <div class="hero-actions">
    <a href="#apply" class="btn-primary">Apply for the Founding Cohort</a>
    <a href="#programme" class="btn-ghost">See the Programme</a>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-foot">
    <span class="founding-tag">Founding cohort · {FOUNDING_SPOTS_REMAINING} spots remaining</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ICEBERG DIAGRAM -->
<section class="iceberg-section">
  <div class="iceberg-inner reveal">
    <span class="section-tag">The Method, in One Image</span>
    <h2>Budgets live above the waterline.<br /><em>The real work is below.</em></h2>

    <div class="iceberg-figure" aria-label="Iceberg diagram — behaviour above the waterline, the story beneath it below">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 600 460" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="ice-above" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#F5F0E8" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#E8D5B0" />
          </linearGradient>
          <linearGradient id="ice-below" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#1C2A3A" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#141F2B" />
          </linearGradient>
          <linearGradient id="water" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#C4A265" stop-opacity="0.55" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#C4A265" stop-opacity="0.0" />
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>

        <!-- Above-waterline iceberg (tip) -->
        <polygon points="260,50 340,50 370,170 230,170" fill="url(#ice-above)" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="1.5" />

        <!-- Waterline -->
        <line x1="40" y1="175" x2="560" y2="175" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 5" />
        <rect x="40" y="175" width="520" height="8" fill="url(#water)" />

        <!-- Below-waterline iceberg (mass) -->
        <polygon points="230,175 370,175 430,380 170,380" fill="url(#ice-below)" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.95" />

        <!-- Subtle highlight lines on the submerged mass -->
        <path d="M 200 220 L 260 215" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.35" />
        <path d="M 210 280 L 330 270" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.3" />
        <path d="M 200 340 L 400 335" stroke="#C4A265" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.25" />

        <!-- Labels ABOVE -->
        <text x="40" y="70" class="ice-label ice-label-above">BEHAVIOUR</text>
        <text x="40" y="92" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">Budgets</text>
        <text x="40" y="112" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">Spreadsheets</text>
        <text x="40" y="132" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">Apps</text>
        <text x="40" y="152" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">Side hustles</text>

        <text x="460" y="70" class="ice-label ice-label-above">VISIBLE</text>
        <text x="460" y="92" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">What you do</text>
        <text x="460" y="112" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">What you track</text>
        <text x="460" y="132" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">What you try</text>
        <text x="460" y="152" class="ice-sub ice-sub-above">Finance books</text>

        <!-- Labels BELOW -->
        <text x="40" y="230" class="ice-label ice-label-below">THE STORY</text>
        <text x="40" y="252" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">The pattern repeating</text>
        <text x="40" y="272" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">The thing you won't look at</text>
        <text x="40" y="292" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">What you learned about money</text>
        <text x="40" y="312" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">before you could name it</text>

        <text x="460" y="230" class="ice-label ice-label-below">INVISIBLE</text>
        <text x="460" y="252" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">Inherited beliefs</text>
        <text x="460" y="272" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">Fear of looking</text>
        <text x="460" y="292" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">Shame loops</text>
        <text x="460" y="312" class="ice-sub ice-sub-below">Identity around money</text>

        <!-- Waterline tag -->
        <text x="300" y="168" text-anchor="middle" class="ice-waterline">the waterline</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <p class="iceberg-caption">Most financial advice works above the line. The Money Story Method starts below it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE PROBLEM -->
<section class="problem">
  <div class="problem-inner reveal">
    <span class="section-tag">The Problem</span>
    <h2>It's not the <em>plan.</em><br />It's the wall you hit <em>before</em> the plan.</h2>
    <p>You've downloaded the budget template. You've tried Monzo, YNAB, maybe even a spreadsheet someone built for you. You've asked ChatGPT to make you a plan more than once.</p>
    <p>None of it sticks. Not because the plans are bad. Because every plan assumes you'll sit down calmly and look at your money — and the moment you try, something in you closes the app.</p>
    <p>That's not a discipline problem. It's a pattern one — and it's more common than the finance world admits. This programme is built for that exact gap.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ORIGIN STORY -->
<section class="origin">
  <div class="origin-inner reveal">
    <span class="section-tag">Origin</span>
    <h2>Why I built <em>the method.</em></h2>
    <div class="origin-body">
      <p>I spent years in financial services at AAGSJP. I built plans that made perfect sense on paper. Then I watched client after client nod, take the plan home, and change nothing.</p>
      <p>That's not a willpower problem. That's a story problem — and nothing in my training was set up to see it, let alone work with it.</p>
      <p>So I went and got an MSc in Behavioural Economics. I wanted to understand, properly, why the gap between knowing and doing is so wide when it comes to money. What I learned is that the plan is almost never the issue. It's what's running underneath it — the things you learned about money before you could name them, the story you've been inside so long you stopped noticing it.</p>
      <p>The Money Story Method is what I built to do that work underneath first. Once the story shifts, the plan finally holds.</p>
      <p class="origin-sign">— Joel</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- NAMED ARCHETYPES -->
<section class="archetypes">
  <div class="archetypes-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Three Patterns I See</span>
      <h2>You probably recognise <em>one of these.</em></h2>
      <p class="archetypes-intro">These are the surface shapes. The quiz below names the deeper script running the pattern — the thing that has to shift before anything else will.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="archetype-grid reveal">
      <div class="archetype-card">
        <span class="arch-num">01</span>
        <h3>The Drifter</h3>
        <p>Earning well. Aimless. Money moves through, nothing accumulates. Not in crisis — just not building. Years go by and the numbers look roughly the same as they did three jobs ago.</p>
        <p class="arch-sound">Sound familiar?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="archetype-card">
        <span class="arch-num">02</span>
        <h3>The Over-Achiever</h3>
        <p>Hitting every external marker. Salary up, title up, postcode up. Still feels empty when the lights go off. The number on the screen goes up; the feeling doesn't move.</p>
        <p class="arch-sound">Sound familiar?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="archetype-card">
        <span class="arch-num">03</span>
        <h3>The Avoider</h3>
        <p>Won't open the banking app. Has the income to build something real, can't bring himself to look. The longer he doesn't look, the worse the looking gets — so he doesn't.</p>
        <p class="arch-sound">Sound familiar?</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="archetypes-quiz reveal">
      <p>The quiz below names the deeper script running the pattern.</p>
      <a href={LINKS.quiz} class="btn-ghost-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Take the Money Beliefs Quiz &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO THIS IS FOR / NOT FOR (merged) -->
<section class="forwho">
  <div class="forwho-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Fit Check</span>
      <h2>Is this <em>for you</em> — or not?</h2>
      <p class="forwho-intro">I'd rather say no early than oversell the work. Two honest columns.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="forwho-grid">
      <div class="forwho-col forwho-for reveal">
        <h3>Who this <em>is</em> for</h3>
        <p class="forwho-sub">If several of these land, the programme is probably right for you. None of them make you broken — they make you human, and they're the exact patterns the programme works with.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>You've tried budgets and apps and none of them have stuck for more than a few weeks</li>
          <li>You feel dread, avoidance, or flatness when you open your banking app — or you avoid it entirely</li>
          <li>You've had the impulse-spend-then-regret cycle more times than you want to count</li>
          <li>Your income is irregular or you're self-employed, and the uncertainty is exhausting</li>
          <li>You grew up watching money cause stress or conflict — and you've never quite shaken that feeling</li>
          <li>You want to feel <em>steady</em> with money, not just technically good at managing it</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="forwho-col forwho-notfor reveal">
        <h3>Who this is <em>not</em> for</h3>
        <p class="forwho-sub">Being honest — this isn't for everyone. If any of these are you, I'd rather point you somewhere better than take your money.</p>
        <ul class="notlist">
          <li>If your main challenge is "I need to earn more", this isn't that programme. Behavioural coaching won't fix an income problem.</li>
          <li>If you want a get-rich-quick framework, hustle strategies, or "manifest abundance" language, I'm not the right coach. I'll never use that language and it won't be in the work.</li>
          <li>If you're looking for pure financial advice — regulated product recommendations, pension specifics — that's a different service. This programme sits upstream: the behaviour that makes advice actually land.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE PROGRAMME -->
<section class="programme" id="programme">
  <div class="programme-inner">
    <div class="reveal section-head">
      <span class="section-tag">The Programme</span>
      <h2>Four phases.<br />Twelve weeks.<br /><em>One coherent story.</em></h2>
      <p class="programme-intro">The programme moves in a deliberate order — safety before opportunity, understanding before action. Nothing is rushed. Each phase builds on what came before.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase timeline diagram -->
    <div class="timeline reveal" aria-label="12-week programme timeline">
      <div class="timeline-track"></div>
      <div class="timeline-fill"></div>
      <div class="timeline-points">
        <div class="tl-point">
          <div class="tl-circle"><span>1</span></div>
          <div class="tl-label">
            <span class="tl-weeks">Weeks 1–3</span>
            <span class="tl-name">Discover</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-point">
          <div class="tl-circle"><span>2</span></div>
          <div class="tl-label">
            <span class="tl-weeks">Weeks 4–5</span>
            <span class="tl-name">Understand</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-point">
          <div class="tl-circle"><span>3</span></div>
          <div class="tl-label">
            <span class="tl-weeks">Weeks 6–8</span>
            <span class="tl-name">Rewrite</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-point">
          <div class="tl-circle"><span>4</span></div>
          <div class="tl-label">
            <span class="tl-weeks">Weeks 9–12</span>
            <span class="tl-name">Build</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phases">
      <div class="phase reveal">
        <div class="phase-marker">
          <span class="phase-num">Phase 1</span>
          <span class="phase-weeks">Weeks 1–3</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Discover</h3>
        <p class="phase-lead">The money story you inherited, before anyone asked you if you wanted it.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Map the origin of your relationship with money — family patterns, early memories, inherited scripts</li>
          <li>Surface the beliefs currently running underneath your financial behaviour (most are invisible until named)</li>
          <li>Identify your dominant <em>money script</em> — Avoidance, Worship, Status, or Vigilance — using validated frameworks</li>
          <li>Write your Financial Literacy Self-Assessment so Phases 3 and 4 are tailored to you specifically</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase reveal">
        <div class="phase-marker">
          <span class="phase-num">Phase 2</span>
          <span class="phase-weeks">Weeks 4–5</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Understand</h3>
        <p class="phase-lead">The patterns underneath the behaviour. The knowing-doing gap, named and explained.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The <em>Behavioural Pattern Report</em> — a personalised document mapping which cognitive biases most influence your decisions</li>
          <li>Loss aversion, status quo bias, mental accounting, default effect — applied directly to your life</li>
          <li>Why willpower has failed you, and what actually works with how your brain is wired</li>
          <li>A spending autopilot map — the triggers and contexts that quietly run your financial day</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase reveal">
        <div class="phase-marker">
          <span class="phase-num">Phase 3</span>
          <span class="phase-weeks">Weeks 6–8</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Rewrite</h3>
        <p class="phase-lead">Challenge the beliefs that no longer serve you. Write new ones you actually chose.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Structured belief challenge — the limiting narratives identified in Phase 1, tested and replaced</li>
          <li>Your <em>Rewrite Document</em> — your new money story, in your own words</li>
          <li>Behavioural guardrails — specific anchors for the moments that usually derail you</li>
          <li>Permission work — the language you'll need to say yes and no to money decisions without the old shame</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase reveal">
        <div class="phase-marker">
          <span class="phase-num">Phase 4</span>
          <span class="phase-weeks">Weeks 9–12</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Build</h3>
        <p class="phase-lead">The practical system — built around how your brain actually works, not how you wish it did.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your <em>Behavioural Financial Plan</em> — budget, savings, debt strategy, investing approach, tailored to your psychology</li>
          <li>Financial literacy teaching dialled in to your specific gaps (high confidence areas get quick mention, weak areas get full coverage)</li>
          <li>Three-Paths Framework for major decisions — never white-knuckle another money choice</li>
          <li>Graduation Story — a complete record of the work, yours to keep forever</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT YOU GET -->
<section class="whatyouget">
  <div class="whatyouget-inner">
    <div class="reveal section-head">
      <span class="section-tag">What's Included</span>
      <h2>The programme, plus the <em>private portal.</em></h2>
      <p class="wyg-intro">Every client gets access to a bespoke portal I built for this method. Everything in one place — sessions, worksheets, deliverables, direct messaging.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="inclusions reveal">
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">01</span>
        <h3>Twelve weekly 1:1 sessions</h3>
        <p>60-minute Zoom calls, same day each week where possible. Recorded if you want them to be.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">02</span>
        <h3>Personalised deliverables</h3>
        <p>Your Money Story Profile, Behavioural Pattern Report, Rewrite Document, and Behavioural Financial Plan — all documents written specifically for you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">03</span>
        <h3>The interactive worksheets</h3>
        <p>Eleven structured exercises built into the portal. Not PDFs you print and lose — real interactive forms with your responses saved forever.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">04</span>
        <h3>Direct messaging between sessions</h3>
        <p>Something comes up on Tuesday? Message me. No waiting until Thursday for a 5-minute thing. No inbox chaos either.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">05</span>
        <h3>Financial Literacy Library</h3>
        <p>Eight modules covering income, spending, saving, debt, investing, protection, retirement, and decision-making. Yours forever after graduation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="inclusion">
        <span class="inclusion-num">06</span>
        <h3>Mobile app experience</h3>
        <p>Install the portal to your home screen on iPhone or Android. Push notifications for sessions, reminders, and new deliverables.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- INSIDE THE PORTAL (screenshots) -->
<section class="portal-preview">
  <div class="portal-preview-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Inside the Portal</span>
      <h2>A real product,<br /><em>not a folder of PDFs.</em></h2>
      <p class="portal-preview-intro">I built the portal specifically for this method. Every worksheet is interactive, every deliverable is markdown-styled, every session summary is searchable. Once you're in, everything lives in one place.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="portal-shots reveal">
      <figure class="shot">
        <img src="/images/portal-dashboard.png" alt="Coach dashboard showing active clients, phase, and engagement" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Coach dashboard — one glance, every client</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="shot">
        <img src="/images/portal-worksheet.png" alt="Interactive worksheet mid-fill — WoW Money Beliefs Inventory" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Interactive worksheets — never a PDF you lose</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="shot">
        <img src="/images/portal-deliverable.png" alt="Deliverable editor — Behavioural Pattern Report being drafted" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Personalised deliverables — written for you</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PILLARS (shortened to 3-line strip) -->
<section class="pillars-strip" id="approach">
  <div class="pillars-strip-inner reveal">
    <span class="section-tag">How I Work</span>
    <div class="pillars-line">
      <span><em>Safety</em> before opportunity</span>
      <span class="pillars-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
      <span><em>Empathy</em> before advice</span>
      <span class="pillars-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
      <span><em>Science</em> before opinion</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- AUTHORITY STACK -->
<section class="authority">
  <div class="authority-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Authority Stack</span>
      <h2>Grounded in the research <em>that matters.</em></h2>
      <p class="authority-intro">This isn't invented. The method sits on top of four bodies of peer-reviewed work, plus a postgraduate degree trained in applying them. If a tool or framework shows up in a session, it came from here — not from an Instagram carousel.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="authority-grid reveal">
      <div class="auth-card">
        <span class="auth-num">01</span>
        <h3>Klontz Money Scripts</h3>
        <p>Dr Brad Klontz's validated inventory of the four underlying money beliefs — Avoidance, Worship, Status, Vigilance. The framework sitting under the quiz and Phase 1.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="auth-card">
        <span class="auth-num">02</span>
        <h3>Kahneman &amp; Tversky</h3>
        <p>Prospect theory. Loss aversion. The asymmetry between the pain of losing and the pleasure of gaining. The reason most financial decisions aren't made the way economists assume.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="auth-card">
        <span class="auth-num">03</span>
        <h3>Richard Thaler</h3>
        <p>Behavioural finance. Mental accounting, the endowment effect, nudge architecture. Why the structure around a decision matters as much as the decision.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="auth-card">
        <span class="auth-num">04</span>
        <h3>Charles Duhigg</h3>
        <p>Habit loop research — cue, routine, reward. The reason willpower fails and the reason behavioural guardrails work. The spine of Phase 4.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="authority-note reveal">MSc Behavioural Economics (UK) — trained specifically in applying these frameworks to real financial behaviour. Not a certification anyone can buy in a weekend.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PROOF / SOCIAL PROOF (placeholder while pre-launch) -->
<section class="proof">
  <div class="proof-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Founding Cohort</span>
      <h2>Early work, <em>early clients.</em></h2>
      <p class="proof-cohort-line">Founding cohort · {FOUNDING_SPOTS_REMAINING} spots remaining · <span class="proof-applicants">[placeholder: {FOUNDING_APPLICANTS} applicants on the list]</span></p>
      <p class="proof-intro">The testimonials below are placeholders — marked clearly. They're here so the page reads the way it will once real founding-cohort work is finished. Real, named quotes will replace them as clients graduate.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="testimonials reveal">
      <figure class="testimonial">
        <span class="testimonial-tag">[ placeholder — not a real client ]</span>
        <blockquote>
          <p>I'd been drifting for about six years. Good income, nothing to show for it, vaguely embarrassed about it whenever anyone asked. The work in Phase 1 cracked open something I hadn't looked at since I was about fourteen. By the end I had an actual direction — not a budget, a <em>direction</em>. Money started accumulating once I knew what I was accumulating it for.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>James, 31 · London · The Drifter</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="testimonial">
        <span class="testimonial-tag">[ placeholder — not a real client ]</span>
        <blockquote>
          <p>I came in wanting "a plan". I left realising I'd been using plans to avoid a conversation with myself. The goalposts I'd been chasing weren't mine — they were inherited, and hitting them never changed the feeling in my chest. Joel didn't try to talk me out of ambition. He helped me aim it somewhere I actually wanted to be.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>Rhys, 34 · Manchester · The Over-Achiever</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="testimonial">
        <span class="testimonial-tag">[ placeholder — not a real client ]</span>
        <blockquote>
          <p>I hadn't opened my main banking app properly in about two years. The idea of looking made me feel ill. What worked wasn't being pushed to look — it was understanding <em>why</em> I couldn't, and going slower than any other finance thing I'd ever tried. By Week 6 I was opening the app without a knot in my stomach. That alone was worth the programme.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>Daniel, 29 · Bristol · The Avoider</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PRICING -->
<section class="pricing">
  <div class="pricing-inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="section-tag">Investment</span>
      <h2>Founding cohort pricing.<br /><em>First 10 paying clients.</em></h2>
      <div class="price-anchor">
        <span class="anchor-item anchor-was"><s>£997</s><span>Standard price</span></span>
        <span class="anchor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <span class="anchor-item anchor-is"><strong>£597</strong><span>Founding cohort · You save £400</span></span>
      </div>
      <p class="pricing-intro">This is the founding price. It rises to £847 for the next 10 clients, then £997 after that. Lock in £597 now and it's yours for this programme and any future version you join.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="plans reveal">
      <div class="plan">
